<br><br>
<em>Figure 5: Consecutive dry days in August 2018 (Based on E-OBS)</em>
<br><br>
<h2>The weather in August 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
Daily minimum, average, and maximum temperatures were exceptionally above the 1981-2010 average throughout Europe. Also in the four preceding months April to July most of Europe was warmer than normal, except parts of Southern Europe. However, in August also Southern Europe was warmer than normal. In Northwest and Southeast Europe the maximum temperatures were near average. The coldest night was below normal in large parts of France and Germany, although in these regions the monthly mean minimum temperature was much above normal. The geographical pattern of the warmest day temperature was similar to that of the monthly mean maximum temperature.
